cs.WEB, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MOBILE

Reasoning: 
- cs.WEB is the most likely category as the paper focuses on investigating the impact of Android's battery-saver mode on mobile Web performance metrics. 
- cs.OS is also likely as the paper discusses the CPU throttling mechanism of Android's battery-saver mode. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper analyzes the impact of a system-level feature (battery-saver mode) on mobile Web performance. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is possible as the paper discusses the impact of CPU clock speed on webpage load process. 
- cs.MOBILE is also possible as the paper specifically focuses on the impact of battery-saver mode on mobile devices.
